readme:
Service Usage

The service communicates examination status to the relevant backend Health provider system at business significant points in the examination life-cycle.
For a Front End Loaded (FEL) Health Case, a response from SV445 must have been successfully processed before SV441 can be used.
The service is initiated upon the following business triggers:
At the commencement of a health examination.
Upon placing the health examination on hold due to pregnancy
Upon placing the an up front medical / front end loaded health examination on hold due to pregnancy
Upon the DMP/DR/PR saying the client is not returning to complete the examinations.
Suspected active TB (Australian only)
Upon the case first being picked up by a clinic
Upon the case being unlinked by the last clinic
The Health Case will be updated to reflect the change in examination status in eMedical.
Health Status Update is also used by eMed to inform USG of a class 'A' tuberculosis case via a new calue 'CLASS A TB' - added for BRNOV17
Asynchronous service.

Service Behaviour

The Health Case will be updated to reflect the change in examination status in eMedical.
Asynchronous service.

Service Dependencies

XS015 is the externally dependent service that acts as a proxy for SV441.
No transform exists so the payload of SV441 is directly exposed via XS015 but in a flattened form.
